 in health care must start with the development of safe, respectful, and caring relationships between doctors and patients. It serves as a strong reminder that the way we care for those who suffer most reveals who we are as a society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 0aAdult child abuse victimsxMental health. 0aChild abusexPsychological aspects. 0aPsychic trauma. 0aPsychotherapist and patient. 4aDISCOUNT-C. 7aMEDICAL / Physician & Patient.2bisacsh  aPTSD.  aadverse childhood experiences.  abedside manner.  acare.  achild abuse.  achildhood trauma.  acounselling.  adoctor-patient relationships.  aempathy.  afamily medicine.  ahealth care.  amental health.  apsychology.  apsychotherapy.1 aHunter, MD, Jonathan, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073922040uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148752836240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487528362423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487528362/original  a978-3-11-073922-0  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aEBA_CL_MDPM  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MDPM  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK